<p>Hi team,</p>

<p>We have two layout options for how the <strong>Meet the Team</strong> section is organized. Everything else on the page (Hero, Overview, Trials, Sidebar) is identical between the two versions.</p>

<h2>V4 &mdash; Stacked Sections</h2>
<p><a class="link" href="https://askit-inc.github.io/spotlight-series-microsite/#/spotlight-v4">https://askit-inc.github.io/spotlight-series-microsite/#/spotlight-v4</a></p>
<ul>
<li>Team is shown as <strong>two stacked sections</strong> on one page</li>
<li>&ldquo;Meet the Team &mdash; Main Site&rdquo; appears first, then &ldquo;Meet the Team &mdash; Endeavor Site&rdquo; below</li>
<li>User scrolls through all providers in one long list</li>
</ul>

<h2>V5 &mdash; Equal Tabs (Recommended)</h2>
<p><a class="link" href="https://askit-inc.github.io/spotlight-series-microsite/#/spotlight-v5">https://askit-inc.github.io/spotlight-series-microsite/#/spotlight-v5</a></p>
<ul>
<li>Team uses <strong>two equal tabs</strong> with institution logos: <strong>UChicago Medicine</strong> | <strong>Endeavor Health</strong></li>
<li>Tabs are visually equal &mdash; no hierarchy implied, neither site appears &ldquo;above&rdquo; the other</li>
<li>User clicks a tab to switch between teams (no extra scrolling)</li>
<li>Dr. Sarswat appears in both tabs since she leads across both institutions</li>
</ul>

<h2>Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Feature</th><th>V4 (Stacked)</th><th>V5 (Tabs)</th></tr>
<tr><td>Layout</td><td>Two sections, one below the other</td><td>Two equal tabs, click to switch</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hierarchy</td><td>UChicago appears first (top), Endeavor below</td><td>Equal &mdash; neither is &ldquo;above&rdquo; the other</td></tr>
<tr><td>Scrolling</td><td>Long page, scroll through both teams</td><td>Compact &mdash; only one team visible at a time</td></tr>
<tr><td>Branding</td><td>Text labels only</td><td>Institution favicon icons + text</td></tr>
<tr><td>Dr. Sarswat</td><td>Listed in both sections</td><td>Listed in both tabs</td></tr>
<tr><td>Partnership signal</td><td>Could imply Endeavor is secondary</td><td>Presents as equal partners</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="recommend">
<strong>&#9989; Recommendation:</strong> V5 (Tabs) presents Endeavor as an equal partner rather than a sub-section listed below UChicago. It&rsquo;s cleaner, requires less scrolling, and patients can quickly find their location&rsquo;s team. This aligns with the &ldquo;shared site&rdquo; approach discussed.
</div>

<p>Please review both and let me know which direction you&rsquo;d like to go with.</p>

<p>Thanks,<br>Sukh</p>

